body: 9 (return) [ Aurelius Victor censures the negligence of his sovereign in choosing the governors of the provinces, and the generals of the army, and concludes his history with a very bold observation, as it is much more dangerous under a feeble reign to attack the ministers than the master himself. ÒUti verum absolvam brevi, ut Imperatore ipso clarius ita apparitorum plerisque magis atrox nihil.Ó]
